# Desktop portable + installer (develop together)

The **only** bundled app tree is `desktop\app\`. It is rebuilt from root sources — never edit `desktop\app\` by hand.

| Command | When | Output |
|---------|------|--------|
| `npm run desktop:sync` | After backend/frontend/launcher changes (runs automatically in `commit.bat`) | Updates `desktop\app\` |
| `npm run dist` | When user tests portable/installer or asks to package | Portable + installer together |

## After code changes

1. `commit.bat` runs `sync-desktop-app.ps1` automatically.
2. If the user mentions **portable**, **installer**, **desktop**, or **distribution**, also run:
   ```powershell
   npm run dist
   ```
   This builds **both**:
   - Portable: `desktop\release\win-unpacked\QS Assistant.exe`
   - Installer: `dist\installer\QS-Assistant-Setup.exe`

## Do not use stale paths

- Do **not** rely on committed files under `desktop\app\` (gitignored).
- Legacy `scripts\package-windows.ps1` + Inno `installer\QS-Assistant.iss` are optional; primary path is **electron-builder** (`npm run dist`).

## Source of truth

| Source | Copied to |
|--------|-----------|
| `backend\` | `desktop\app\backend\` |
| `frontend\dist\` | `desktop\app\backend\frontend-dist\` |
| `launcher\*.ps1` | `desktop\app\launcher\` |
